🔹 5️⃣ #elif (Else If)
👉 Used when checking multiple conditions.

Example:
#include <stdio.h>

#define VALUE 3

int main() {

#if VALUE == 1
    printf("Value is 1\n");

#elif VALUE == 2
    printf("Value is 2\n");

#elif VALUE == 3
    printf("Value is 3\n");

#else
    printf("Unknown value\n");

#endif

    return 0;
}
Output:

Value is 3
🔹 6️⃣ #undef
👉 Used to remove a macro definition.

Example:
#include <stdio.h>

#define FLAG

#undef FLAG

int main() {

#ifdef FLAG
    printf("Flag is defined\n");
#else
    printf("Flag is NOT defined\n");
#endif

    return 0;
}
Output:

Flag is NOT defined
Because we removed it using #undef.

🔥 Important: Order of Execution
Preprocessor runs first:

Handles #define

Checks #ifdef, #if

Removes unwanted code

Then compiler compiles remaining code

